# Putting code between `{` and `}` creates a block. Blocks can be applied by
# calling `apply`, to execute the code within them.
{ 1 } apply 1 = assert

# TASK: Create binding from block, apply later, demonstrating that blocks are
#       values.
# TASK: Demonstrate nested blocks. Actually, demonstrate that any syntax on the
#       top level is also valid within a block.
# TASK: Demonstrate that applying a block might require type annotations.
